title: Salaheddine Aqqal
text:
Salaheddine Aqqal (born 22 August 1984) is a <a href="Morocco">Moroccan</a> <a href="Association%20football">football</a> midfielder. He currently plays in <a href="Morocco">Morocco</a> for <a href="Raja%20Casablanca">Raja Casablanca</a>.
Aqqal played for the Moroccan team in the Under-20 African Nations Cup in 2003. In 2004, he was playing for <a href="Olympic%20Club%20de%20Khouribga">Olympic Club de Khouribga</a> (OCK). He was part of the Moroccan <a href="2004%20Summer%20Olympics">2004 Olympic</a> football team, who exited in the first round, finishing third in group D, behind group winners <a href="Iraq">Iraq</a> and runners-up <a href="Costa%20Rica">Costa Rica</a>. In 2005, he captained the Moroccan team at the <a href="2005%20Mediterranean%20Games">Mediterranean Games</a> in <a href="Almer%C3%ADa">Almería</a>.
